"The patch removes the `!damon_is_running()` check in `damon_call()`. If a caller calls `damon_call()` on a newly allocated context (where `kzalloc` initializes `call_controls_obsolete = false`) before `damon_start()` has successfully started the thread, `damon_call()` will enqueue the request and block indefinitely on `wait_for_completion()`. Previously, the `!damon_is_running(ctx)` check would catch this and safely return `-EINVAL`. To prevent this regression and ensure safe API boundaries, `call_controls_obsolete` should be initialized to `true` in `damon_new_ctx()`, so that it blocks requests until the thread actually sets it to `false` upon startup."
